  "prompt": "How common is dying in your sleep?",
  "response": "Dying in your sleep, often referred to as \"natural causes\" or due to underlying health issues such as heart conditions, stroke, or other age-related illnesses, is relatively common among the elderly. It's a less traumatic way to pass compared to other forms of death and is often considered peaceful.\n\nHowever, the exact prevalence can vary based on factors such as age, health status, and medical advancements. For instance, elderly individuals are more likely to die in their sleep due to diminishing health, whereas it's rarer for younger, healthy individuals.\n\nStatistics on this specific type of death are not typically isolated in general mortality data. Instead, deaths are categorized by specific medical conditions, so getting an exact figure can be challenging. Nonetheless, it remains a common occurrence due to the prevalence of cardiovascular diseases and other chronic conditions in older populations.",
